##Step 1: Installing the required libraries


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
pacman::p_load(tidyverse)
```
:::


### Importing the required data


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
exam_data <- read_csv("data/Exam_data.csv")
```
:::


##Step 2: View the data in histogram


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
hist(exam_data$MATHS)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=10, 
                 boundary = 100,
                 color="black", 
                 fill="grey") +
  ggtitle("Distribution of Maths scores")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-2.png){width=672}
:::
:::


##Step 3: Essential Grammatical Elements in ggplot2 with Aesthetic Mapping


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


## Visualising data in Histogram


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x=RACE)) +
  geom_bar()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


## Visualising data in Dotplot


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_dotplot(binwidth=2.5,         
               dotsize = 0.5) +      
  scale_y_continuous(NULL,           
                     breaks = NULL)  
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


## Visualising data in Histogram in bins


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram()       
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-7-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### Adding colors


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, 
           fill = GENDER)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=20, 
                 color="grey30")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-8-1.png){width=672}
