## Working with Essential Grammatical Elements in ggplot2: stat

### Working with stat summary


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS, x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  stat_summary(geom = "point",       
               fun="mean",         
               colour ="red",        
               size=4)               
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-14-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### Overriding soothing methods


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, 
           y=ENGLISH)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, 
              size=0.5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-15-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


## Working with Essential Grammatical Elements in ggplot2: Facet

### Using Facetwraps


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=20) +
    facet_wrap(~ CLASS)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-16-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### Using Facet Grid


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=20) +
    facet_grid(~ CLASS)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](hands_on_ex1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-17-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::
